Suppose random sample size \(n\) drawn population, measurements \((x_{i1}, x_{i2}...x_{ik}, y_i)\) \(= 1, ... , n\), obtained n individuals.random variables \(x_{i1}, x_{i2}...x_{ik}\) commonly termed predictor variables (simply, predictors), depending field application, may also called independent variables, regressors, features, covariates explanatory variables.\(y_i\) variable called response variable (simply, response). terms include target variable, variate, dependent variable outcome variable.Linear Regression Model represents relation response variable \(y\) predictor variables \(x_{1}, x_{2}...x_{k}\) (lowercase notation simplicity) form:\[
\begin{align}
y = \beta_0 + \beta_1 + ... + \beta_k + \epsilon
\end{align}
\]\(\beta_0, ..., \beta_k\) constants regression coefficients, \(\epsilon\) random error term follows normal distribution mean zero (\(\mu = 0\)) constant variance \(\sigma^2\). , \(\epsilon \sim Norm(\mu = 0, \sigma^2)\). Also, random errors assumed independent different individuals sample.parameters model \(\beta_0, ..., \beta_k\), variance \(\sigma^2\) unknown estimated sample data.Note relationship predictors response necessarily linear, polynomial interaction terms may included, necessarily linear beta coefficients. , relationship modeled linear combination parameters.Note , general linear regression model, response variable y normal distribution mean:\[
\begin{align}
\mathbb{E}(y) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \cdot x_1 + ... + \beta_k \cdot x_k
\end{align}
\]
